  <section class="faq-section">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Texas AI Data Centers</h2>
    <details open>
      <summary>What are Texas AI Data Centers?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Texas AI data centers are large facilities that house powerful computers used to train and run artificial intelligence systems. They process massive amounts of data for cloud services, automation, and machine learning applications.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why are so many AI data centers being built in Texas?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Texas offers abundant land, relatively low electricity costs, a business-friendly regulatory environment, and existing power infrastructure — making it an attractive location for large-scale AI infrastructure investment.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do AI data centers affect the Texas power grid?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Yes. AI data centers consume enormous amounts of electricity, and their rapid expansion is placing significant strain on the ERCOT grid, raising concerns about reliability and costs for all Texas residents.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Do AI data centers use a lot of water?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Many data centers use water-based cooling systems that can consume millions of gallons per day. In water-stressed regions of Texas, this raises serious concerns about long-term water availability for residents and agriculture.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How do AI data centers impact local communities?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Communities near data centers often experience increased truck traffic, 24/7 construction noise, changes to rural land character, and rising infrastructure costs — while the promised economic benefits don't always materialise locally.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Where can I stay updated on new developments?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">Sign up on our <a href="/stay-informed">Stay Informed</a> page to receive updates on new data center projects, policy changes, and community impacts across Texas.</div>
    </details>
  </section>

  <div class="closing">
    <p>Texas residents need to understand how this explosive growth in AI infrastructure will affect energy costs, the power grid, and local communities. Stay informed — the changes coming in the next few years will impact everyone.</p>
  </div>
<script>
  const details = document.querySelectorAll('details');
  details.forEach(detail => {
    detail.addEventListener('toggle', () => {
      if (detail.open) {
        details.forEach(other => {
          if (other !== detail) other.open = false;
        });
      }
    });
  });
</script>
